

// Lazy Loading 

// lazy loading hibernate hit the database when we attempt to call get() over any persistent object


case 1: 
    Hibernate does egar loading in case direct property 
    
    public class Product {
	
	@Id
	@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.AUTO)
	private int pid;
	private String name;
	private int unitcost;
	private int sellingPrice;
	}
	
	session.openSession();
	Product p = session.get(Product.class,1); 
	session.close();
	String name = p.getName(); // we will get the values 
								// this is the direct property , not in any mapping

case 2: 

   hibernate does the Egar loading 
    a) oneToOne & 
    b) ManyToOne    mapping
    
 other than case 2 mapping all have done through : LazyLoading
						